{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9413eb5d-055c-4b5c-983c-c8fafb43f64d","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the newer test runner). With `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled in your project, `dotnet run` launches the testing platform directly, which supports hot reload — it watches for file changes and re-runs affected tests automatically.\n\n`dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest adapter layer and **does not** support the hot reload extension.\n\nSo run:\n```\nTESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED=1 dotnet run\n```\n(or set the env var beforehand, then just `dotnet run`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ddca4df0-9337-462e-b030-be9935bcfec4","outputTokens":165,"requestId":"340A:3A1698:B661C8:D6614E:69F40598"},"id":"68df9987-b74b-4e50-a16b-c7d3bb55c5d2","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:45:03.634Z","parentId":"a340f60d-449c-43c4-834a-afe74d9b14fe"}
